3. If two microservices are there and A depends on B, how would you run them?


# STANDARD SELF READINESS PROBE - Checks A's own /health endpoint only
readinessProbe:
  httpGet:
    path: /health
    port: 8080
  initialDelaySeconds: 5
  periodSeconds: 10

# DEPENDENCY READINESS PROBE - Checks B service's /health endpoint (host: b-service)
readinessProbe:
  httpGet:
    path: /health
    port: 8080
    host: b-service            # Points to B service so this check only pod b /health path , and so nocheck for pod a here but u can add after this .
  initialDelaySeconds: 10
  periodSeconds: 5

# DIFFERENCE: Standard=Self-check (A ready when A healthy); Dependency=Waits for B (A unready until B responds OK)
